context: English Breakfast Loose Leaf Tea is a full-bodied blend by Taylors of Harrogate, offering a rich and refreshing taste with a bright color. Enjoyable at any time, it's made from black tea leaves and comes in an elegant, reusable 4.41 ounce tin. Carbon Neutral Certified and Ethical Tea Partnership member.
content:
Fantastic flavor
I've recently delved into the world of loose-leaf teas, and Taylors of Harrogate Earl Grey has been a delightful discovery.
The aroma that wafts from the tin is a symphony of bergamot, a fragrant citrus delight. It's not just tea; it's an olfactory experience that sets the stage for the tea journey ahead.
The loose leaves are a visual treat, a blend of quality black tea leaves and bergamot oil. The brewing process is a spectacle as the leaves unfurl, releasing their full flavor potential. The result is a cup of Earl Grey that dances on the palate with a perfect balance of robust tea and the zesty notes of bergamot.
What sets Taylors of Harrogate apart is the attention to detail. The tin is not just packaging; it's a nod to the brand's commitment to preserving the freshness of the tea. The resealable lid ensures each scoop maintains its aromatic allure.
Whether you're a seasoned tea connoisseur or a novice looking to embark on a tea adventure, this loose-leaf Earl Grey is a must-try. , Taylors of Harrogate Earl Grey Loose Leaf is a sensory journey that every tea lover should embark on. Elevate your tea moments with this exceptional blend.

The other option is to speak with a machine that is useless since it is an automated and terrible service that is not helpful at all.

context: MacBook Pro 2023 is a powerful laptop equipped with the M3 Pro chip boasting a 12-core CPU and 18-core GPU, delivering exceptional performance for demanding tasks. Featuring a 14.2-inch Liquid Retina XDR display, 18GB Unified Memory, and 1TB SSD Storage, it offers versatility and compatibility with various apps and devices.
content:
life is good
Unboxing & Design: Standard unboxing, nothing extraordinary. The laptop feels solid, thanks to the unibody aluminum build. Love that ports are back!, but I'm really not a fan of the webcam notch – a larger top bezel or a different design would be better. The space black finish is nice, it appears more like a gunmetal grey in bright light, but in low light or oblique angles it is very black.
Performance: Scores well on geekbench, and cinebench. I haven't had any issues with performance, and vs my old base M1 macbook pro 8gb, its much much harder to summon the beach ball! Apple's gaming claims are a bit overhyped, or premature tho... there's hardly any, and running games through Crossover is okay. Compatibility and performance are ymmv for sure. Get a gaming laptop if you want to game.
Display: The Full array micro led backlight really helps HDR pop on this, and colors are fantastic. But in dark images with small bright highlights you can see some backlight blooming. 120hz refresh is always welcome, but know that macbook displays usually have pretty bad pixel response times so fast moving content tends to blur. Apple should move to OLED displays, this would fix their pixel response and backlight blooming.
Memory & Storage: 18GB RAM does the job well, even for AI model stuff (stable diffusion, up to 13b llama models). The 1TB SSD is adequate, though I would've liked more without the Apple tax... Performance-wise, it's comparable to high-end PCIE4 M.2 NVMe drives.
Battery & Charging: Battery life is good, lasts all day for light tasks, but anything that uses rosetta translation or gpu drains it much faster. Magsafe is great to have back, but the magnet feels too strong - worried it might damage the port or finish over time.
Value: At $2400, it feels a bit overpriced. It's a solid buy for those upgrading from older Macs or Apple enthusiasts. If you're thinking of gaming on this, look elsewhere despite apple's recent boasting. Also, I miss Bootcamp - would been great to have the ARM version of Windows on this.

context: Viajes El Corte Inglés is a travel agency where you can find deals on cheap trips, flights, hotels, vacations, cruises, trains, flight plus hotel, tours, theme parks, Paradores and more.
content:
Una experiencia nefasta, viaje a Jordania para el 14/10/23, se hace seguro amplio (104€) para 8 días, se termina de pagar todo el paquete el día 4/10 y el día 7/10, empieza la guerra en Gaza, vamos a informarnos del el 9/10 y ver que podemos hacer, su respuesta que el mayorista, dice que las rutas siguen funcionando, teníamos miedo porque nadie sabe cómo puede evolucionar. El día 13/10, volvemos a la agencia, después de ver las manifestaciones en Amán y la sugerencia en la embajada española de evitar viajar a Jerash y mar muerto. También se les comenta que una de las personas sufre de cardiopatía isquémica y no es aconsejable que viaje (en principio de placer) con miedo y un aumento de ansiedad muy importante.
La respuesta siempre consultar al mayorista y este no admite ninguna mediación por la OCU, sólo vía judicial.
Nosotros no hemos contratado el viaje con el mayorista, lo hemos contratado en El Corte Inglés, en fin……….No quiero volver a tener relaciones con Viajes El Corte Inglés
translation:
A terrible experience, I travelled to Jordan for 10/14/23, full-trip insurance (104€) for 8 days, paid in full by 10/4, war breaks out in Gaza on 10/7. We were informed on 10/9 and tried to find a solution. Their response from the wholesaler was that the routes were still operational, but we were afraid due to the uncertain evolution. On 10/13, we returned to the agency after seeing protests in Amman and a recommendation from the Spanish embassy to avoid Jerash and the Dead Sea. We also informed them that one person suffered from ischemic cardiopathy and it was not advisable for them to travel (initially for pleasure) because of fear and a significant increase in anxiety.
Their response was always to consult the wholesaler, who did not admit any mediation by OCU, only legal means.
We did not contract the trip with the wholesaler, we contracted it with El Corte Inglés, but anyways... I don't want to have any more dealings with Viajes El Corte Inglés.

context: MacBook Pro 2023 is a powerful laptop equipped with the M3 Pro chip boasting a 12-core CPU and 18-core GPU, delivering exceptional performance for demanding tasks. Featuring a 14.2-inch Liquid Retina XDR display, 18GB Unified Memory, and 1TB SSD Storage, it offers versatility and compatibility with various apps and devices.
content:
MBP 14 vs Alienware M16
Well, I ended up buying both this Macbook Pro and an Alienware M16, since both were on sale for BF 2023. The intention is to only keep the one that works the best for me, if any.
Here is the Alienware M16 config: i7, nVidia RTX 4060, 16GB RAM, 512 GB SSD, 16" Quad HD+ 165Hz screen, 7.2 lbs, $1250.
Price: Alienware is roughly $600 cheaper, so it has the initial advantage here, but price is not necessarily the most critical element.
Weight: The Mac weighs half of what the M16 does and that makes a huge difference if you plan to carry it around. Interestingly enough, the MBP is barely heavier than the Macbook Air 15 M2.
OS: There is no comparison here. MacOS is superior in each and every way, from privacy, to ease of use. It also comes with free Office applications. For my use, I find these to be as good if not better than Microsoft Office, but don't expect Numbers to work with complex functions or spreadsheets.
Gaming: This is limited on the Mac, but Steam and GOG have plenty of older Mac games that work great. Fallout, Indiana Jones, Baldurs Gate, just a few examples. However, for latest games, there is no contest here, Alienware can play anything, although in a 1080p config.
Battery Life: The MBP easily wins this one, with almost 2x the battery life. I get around 4-6 hours on the Alienware and 8-12 on the Mac. The Alienware is noisier because it has to run the fan more often.
Screen: 16" is my ideal screen size, but 14" is not bad either. When displaying a static image, the Mac looks more vibrant. It also helps it's significantly brighter. However - the devil is in the details, as I will explain below.
Screen Response Time: Alienware is 10x faster than the Mac. Is the Mac bad? It really depends on what you plan to use it for, but for a product called 'Pro', a screen response as slow as an iPad is disappointing.
PWM (Pulse Width Modulation): Alienware and Apple have completely different approaches here. Apple went for a cheap display that has pwm flickering. If you are sensitive to pwm, you will get nausea, dizziness and headaches. I had these within 20 minutes of using this. There is no flickering on the Alienware.
Temporal Dithering: There is none on the Alienware. I am not sure if the MBP has it, but Apple tends to use cheap 8bit displays that have to fake having billions of colors, so would expect they did it here too. The symptom you would get is that your eyes are burning. My eyes feel this way, but it could also be due to the much higher brightness on the Mac and my eyes still adjusting to it. Apple doesn't allow turning off neither pwm nor temporal dithering.
Value: While I don't necessarily associate value with price, $600 can buy me a PS5, with a game and extra controller. It's not a small difference. But the deal breaker for me is having to use a screen that will get me feel sick. Most PC manufacturers like Dell/Alienware, Asus, Lenovo, etc have decided to not use pwm and temporal dithering in their laptops, but Apple continues to charge an arm and a leg for cheap display panels. Even if you are not getting headaches from pwm, the long term impact of that constant flickering in our eyes is not known. In my case, it made no sense to me to pay that much more for an inferior product. Good news is that the Macbook Air M2 doesn't have any of these issues, so I may still give that a try.
I am rating the MBP 2* and the Alienware 3* (too heavy to carry around, poor battery life, Windows OS that can pop-up ads on my screen, no free Office application). I will definitely return the MBP, but probably also the Alienware and get a MBA 15" M2 instead.

context: Viajes El Corte Inglés is a travel agency where you can find deals on cheap trips, flights, hotels, vacations, cruises, trains, flight plus hotel, tours, theme parks, Paradores and more.
content:
Engaño Viajes El Corte Inglés en viaje a Egipto
Contraté con Viajes El Corte Inglés un crucero por Nilo en octubre 2023. Me ofrecieron una lista de barcos, categoría B, y luego me convencieron para pagar un suplemento para optar a la categoría C mandándome otra lista de barcos. Una vez analizados los barcos que me podían tocar en la opción C acepto el recargo. Unos días antes del viaje me avisan del barco que me han asignado y no está ni en la lista B ni en la lista C. Yo investigo un poco y en otras webs lo catalogan como A (la peor categoría posible). El Corte Inglés se desentendió, la comercial no quiso hacer nada, ni me devolvieron dinero, no me buscaron otro barco y ni me dieron explicaciones. He puesto una reclamación hace un mes y se desentienden, ni me contestan. Una verdadera vergüenza.
translation:
Deceitful Experience with El Corte Inglés travelling to Egypt
I booked a Nile cruise with El Corte Inglés Travel in October 2023. They offered me a list of boats, category B, and then convinced me to pay an supplement to opt for category C, sending me another list of boats. Once I analyzed the boats that I could get in option C, I accepted the surcharge. A few days before the trip, they informed me of the assigned boat, and it was not in either list B or list C. I did some research and found that other websites categorize it as an A (the worst category possible). El Corte Inglés disclaimed responsibility, the salesperson did not want to do anything, they did not refund me, did not find me another boat, and did not give me explanations. I filed a complaint a month ago, and they ignore me, they do not even answer. A true shame.

content:
Fits two bikes great!

context: Viajes El Corte Inglés is a travel agency where you can find deals on cheap trips, flights, hotels, vacations, cruises, trains, flight plus hotel, tours, theme parks, Paradores and more.
content:
Viajes IMSERSO en El Corte Inglés
El pasado día 31 fuimos a hacer una reserva de los viajes del IMSERSO a la oficina de viajes El Corte Inglés, de la Av Juan Carlos I, 12 Murcia.
Paso a relatar mi experiencia: reservamos viaje para nosotros y 4 familiares, la empleada nos entregó la documentación cobrando la parte de su comisión y también nos ofreció un SEGURO DE CANCELACIÓN, que ya está incluido en el viaje y nos dijo que el primer plazo NO SE PODÍA PAGAR ALLÍ, que lo teníamos que hacer en el plazo de 5 días, cosa que no ha sido posible pues en las entidades colaboradoras solo admiten los pagos 2 días a la semana de 9 a 10:30, cuando llego a la entidad el jueves eran las 11:15 y me dicen que ya no puedo pagar hasta el próximo martes, y el martes ya han transcurrido los 5 días, entonces me voy al cajero y solo admite el pago de la totalidad.
Esta mañana llamo al teléfono de Turismo Social y me informan que el primer plazo lo puedo y debo efectuar en la agencia que he hecho la reserva, también me confirman que el viaje lleva incluido un seguro de confirmación que la agencia nos quería vender.
Esto indica que intentan estafar a los jubilados al ofrecerles el seguro, que muchos lo contratarán ignorantes de que ya está incluido por parte de Turismo Social
translation:
IMSERSO Travel at El Corte Inglés
Last December 31, we went to make a reservation for the IMSERSO travels at the El Corte Inglés travel office, located on Avenida Juan Carlos I, 12 Murcia.
I will now relate my experience: we reserved a trip for ourselves and 4 relatives, the employee handed us the documentation charging her commission and also offered us a CANCELLATION INSURANCE, which is already included in the trip and told us that the first payment COULD NOT BE MADE THERE, that we had to do it within 5 days, but that was not possible because in the collaborating entities they only accept payments 2 days a week from 9 to 10:30, when I arrived at the entity on Thursday it was 11:15 and they told me that I could not pay until the next Tuesday, but by then the 5 days had already passed, so I went to the ATM and it only accepted payment in full.
This morning I called the Turismo Social phone number and they informed me that the first payment can and should be made at the agency where the reservation was made, they also confirmed that the trip includes a confirmation insurance that the agency wanted to sell us.
This indicates that they are trying to scam retirees by offering them insurance, which many will purchase unaware that it is already included by Turismo Social.

context: Cloudflare is an internet security and performance company, offering services like content delivery network (CDN), DDoS mitigation, and DNS management. Trusted by millions of websites, it enhances security, reliability, and speed, protecting against cyber threats and ensuring seamless online experiences for users globally.
content:
Incapace di fare il suo lavoro. Dovrebbero andare a raccogliere patate
Sono rimasto estremamente deluso dall'esperienza offerta da Cloudflare. Avevo sentito parlare di questo servizio come di un'opzione affidabile per garantire accesso fluido ai siti web, ma purtroppo la mia esperienza è stata tutt'altro che positiva.

Una volta entrato nel sito supportato da Cloudflare, mi sono trovato costantemente bloccato in una sorta di loop senza fine. Invece di garantire un accesso regolare e veloce, il servizio sembrava fare di tutto per ostacolare la mia navigazione. Ogni tentativo di accedere al sito veniva accolto da un rimbalzo apparentemente infinito, costringendomi a rifare la coda più e più volte.

Questo non è solo frustrante, ma anche inaccettabile. Mi aspettavo che un servizio come Cloudflare fosse in grado di offrire una soluzione affidabile e efficiente per garantire la sicurezza e la velocità di accesso. Invece, mi sono trovato ad affrontare uno dei peggiori servizi che si possano immaginare.

La mancanza di efficienza e la continua necessità di affrontare problemi di accesso hanno reso l'utilizzo di questo servizio un vero e proprio incubo. Consiglio vivamente di evitare Cloudflare se state cercando un'esperienza utente senza intoppi e un accesso regolare ai siti web. Sono sicuro che esistano alternative più affidabili e efficienti sul mercato.
translation:
Incompetent at doing their job. They should go harvest potatoes
I was extremely disappointed with the experience offered by Cloudflare. I had heard of this service as a reliable option to ensure smooth access to websites, but unfortunately my experience was quite the opposite.

Once I entered the site supported by Cloudflare, I constantly found myself stuck in a never-ending loop. Instead of ensuring regular and fast access, the service seemed to do everything to hinder my browsing. Every attempt to access the site was met with an apparently infinite bounce, forcing me to queue up again and again.

This is not only frustrating, but also unacceptable. I expected a service like Cloudflare to offer a reliable and efficient solution to ensure security and access speed. Instead, I found myself facing one of the worst services one can imagine.

The inefficiency and constant need to deal with access problems have made using this service a real nightmare. I strongly recommend avoiding Cloudflare if you are looking for a smooth user experience and regular access to websites. I'm sure there are more reliable and efficient alternatives on the market.

context: Primor is a retail chain specializing in beauty and personal care products. Operating primarily in Spain, it offers a wide range of cosmetics, skincare, fragrances, and toiletries from various brands. With both physical stores and an online presence, Primor serves customers seeking affordable and quality beauty products.
content:
Falta de interés en tu trabajo.Mala atención al cliente.
Destacar que lo ocurrido fue en Tienda del centro comercial BAHIA SUR,San Fernando ya que yo soy clienta asidua de primor en sus distintas tiendas de la bahía y nunca tuve problema en las anteriores que quedé claro.
El viernes voy a comprar ambientador que siempre lo compro allí,no ubico el lugar pregunto y me dice que no lo tiene ,no muestra interes al final termino yo encontrándolo se lo comunico a la encargada en ningún momento quiso saber la dependienta que se trataba,se limitaba a sonreír y disculpar a la chica con expresiones Será nueva,no se dio cuenta,en ningún momento escuché No volverá a pasar ,Quién era la chica,y Perdona lo ocurrido,simplemente con lo siento yo me hubiese quedado satisfecha pero ese desinterés hacia mi una clienta de tantos años ,creo que no lo merecías.
Evidentemente seguiré comprando en Primor por la calidad de sus productos , evitando entrar lo menos posible en la de Bahía sur .
translation:
Lack of interest in your work. Poor customer service.
Note that the incident occurred at Bahia Sur shopping mall's BAHIA SUR store, San Fernando, as I am a regular customer of Primor's different stores in the bay area and never had a problem before, to made it clear.
On Friday, I went to buy air freshener, which I always buy there, I couldn't find the place, I asked, and they told me they didn't have it. The employee showed no interest, and in the end, I found it myself. I informed the manager, but the employee didn't seem to care. She just smiled and made excuses like "She's new," "She didn't notice," and "I'm sorry." I never heard "It won't happen again," "Who was she?" or "I apologize for what happened." I would have been satisfied with a simple "I'm sorry." However, her lack of interest towards a long-time customer like me was undeserved.
Obviously, I will continue to shop at Primor for the quality of their products, but I will avoid entering the Bahia Sur store as much as possible.

context: Viajes El Corte Inglés is a travel agency where you can find deals on cheap trips, flights, hotels, vacations, cruises, trains, flight plus hotel, tours, theme parks, Paradores and more.
content:
La peor experiencia de nuestras vidas!!!
Compramos mis amigas y yo cuatro viajes on line en el corte inglés , a new York.
Al llegar allí nos encontramos que nos an dejado tiradas sin hotel porque no han pagado y an contratado con spedia..
Nos bloquean en el hotel las tarjetas de crédito. pasándonos pagos de 1300  a 1800 euros.
Llamamos a España al corte inglés y no nos atendieron hasta el tercer día de estar en new York.
Pasamos la semana entre reclamaciones , sin poder aprovechar la new York pase.....
Y entre ataques de ansiedad por vernos allí y la impotencia de no poder hacer nada .
Imagínense 4 chicas una semana tiradas en new York en habitaciónes  las cual adjunto de vergüenza  con las maletas de una habitación a otra....
 Al llegar a Madrid lo único que reclamamos son los 4  viajes y las new York pase que salieron casi 300 euros y no pudimos aprovechar.......total 1200 por persona del viaje y el hotel los gastos de la semana allí los asumimos nosotras y nos dicen que nos devuelve 400 par repartir que ya eso nos lo gastamos en llamadas a España para reclamar y lexatin unas cajas ......
De vergüenza pienso sacarlo hasta en los medios de comunicación .
Y desde luego procederemos a la denuncia
translation:
Worst experience of our lives!!!
My friends and I bought 4 online trips to New York from El Corte Inglés.
Upon arriving, we found out that they left us stranded without a hotel because they didn't pay and didn't contract with Spedia..
They blocked our credit cards in the hotel, charging us 1300 to 1800 euros.
We called Spain to El Corte Inglés and they didn't attend to us until the third day of being in New York.
We spent the week making complaints, unable to take advantage of the New York Pass....
And between anxiety attacks from being there and the impotence of not being able to do anything.

Upon returning to Madrid, all we asked for refund was the 4 trips and New York Pass (almost 300 euros) that we couldn't take advantage of...total 1200 per person for the trip and hotel, we had to cover the expenses that week there ourselves and they say they will refund 400 to split, which we already spent on calls to Spain to claim and Lexatin tablets...
I'm ashamed and plan to bring it up in the media.
And of course, we will proceed to file a complaint.

context: Primor is a retail chain specializing in beauty and personal care products. Operating primarily in Spain, it offers a wide range of cosmetics, skincare, fragrances, and toiletries from various brands. With both physical stores and an online presence, Primor serves customers seeking affordable and quality beauty products.
content:
Producto erroneo
Ayer recogí un cubo de palomitas en una tienda primor. Cuando lo compre ponía que podia ser rojo o azul y que le cabían 3,5 L; al abrirlo era amarillo, lo probé porque me pareció muy pequeño, y le cabe un paquete de palomitas a lo justo. Me han enviado un cubo distinto de menor tamaño y menor precio.
He recibido este producto con capacidad de 2,8 L, en vez de 3,5, lo he comprobado con un medidor.
Ya lo he probado para ver la capacidad y no se puede devolver.
Para mi sorpresa no me deja la pagina hacer ningún comentario del producto.
 Me gustaría que me diesen una solución y me reenviasen el producto que he pedido.
 No es el producto que había pedido y me siento estafada. He encontrado el link exacto del producto recibido en Amazon, a un coste mucho inferior.

Actualizo, porque despues de contactar con atención al cliente se han hecho cargo del problema.
translation:
Wrong product
Yesterday I picked up a bucket of popcorn from a Primor store. When I bought it, it said it could be red or blue and that it could hold 3.5 L; when I opened it, it was yellow, I tried it because it seemed very small, and it barely holds a pack of popcorn. I received a different bucket, smaller in size and price.
I received this product with a capacity of 2.8 L, instead of 3.5, I have checked it with a measure.
I have already tried it to see the capacity and it cannot be returned.
To my surprise, the website does not allow me to make any comments on the product.
I would like a solution and for the product I ordered to be resent to me.
It is not the product I ordered and I feel cheated. I have found the exact link of the product received on Amazon, at a much lower cost.

Update, because after contacting customer service, they have taken charge of the problem.

content:
TRUFFATORI
Se solo potessi non mettere stelle lo farei. Sto dal 19 febbraio, sono 10 giorni che aspetto notizie di un’ordine fatto online, ma niente. translation:

Needless to say, I have no more news from their pseudo assistance, they no longer respond and meanwhile I have lost my money. SCAMMERS!

context: Tripadvisor is a travel platform providing reviews, recommendations, and bookings for hotels, restaurants, attractions, and experiences worldwide. Users can browse millions of traveler reviews, compare prices, and make reservations directly through the app.
content:
I didn’t get to finish my review…. Xcaret - Arte
Advice, tips and pointers
If you plan on hitting any of the parks like the ziplines or the ATV rides take the 8:30AM bus to them from Arte. You will be close to the front of the line, you’ll see that because by the time you get to the end of each of those rides some will already be closed because the lines are full. 
If you’re planning on going to the Xcaret park go Mon - Fri if you can - Sat and Sun are a zoo. If you like birds then you must go to the bird sanctuary - it’s hard to describe but you are following a path from top to bottom in a circular fashion bit doesn’t feel like it. There are nets over the top of the exhibit but you don’t notice them and all of the birds are flying free - except the bald eagle and the condor. At each level on the path there are boulders that tell you what birds you can expect to see. And then it just goes on - there are maps there that you can look at to see what you would like to see most. This park can’t be done in one day!! Come here at night and watch the Mexican Show - the first half explains the culture of Mexico and the second half celebrates the different states/provinces of Mexico.
If you only have one week look at what you’d enjoy the most and plan your time. You don’t want to miss the best of what you want to see.

If you’re planning on going to the Xcaret park go Mon - Fri if you can - Sat and Sun are a zoo. context: Primor is a retail chain specializing in beauty and personal care products. Operating primarily in Spain, it offers a wide range of cosmetics, skincare, fragrances, and toiletries from various brands. With both physical stores and an online presence, Primor serves customers seeking affordable and quality beauty products.
content:
Marchant à éviter !!!
Première commande chez ce marchand et très certainement la dernière ! Leurs pratiques commerciales sont déplorables. Au moment de passer commande, j'ai vu qu'ils offraient un flacon d'eau de toilette et un échantillon avec l'achat du parfum que je souhaitais. Cependant, à la réception de ma commande, je suis surpris de constater que le parfum que j'ai acheté était accompagné d'un échantillon et d'un autre produit qui n'avait rien à voir avec l'eau de toilette promise ! J'ai contacté le service client pour me plaindre, et on m'a simplement dit que si le produit n'était pas dans le colis, c'était parce qu'il n'était plus en stock. Ils ne prennent même pas la peine de contacter le client pour le prévenir ! C'est inacceptable. Dans ce cas, ils pourraient mettre n'importe quoi en guise de cadeau pour attirer davantage de commandes et ne pas respecter leurs promesses par la suite ! C'est comme si Amazon vous disait que pour l'achat d'une PS5, vous recevriez gratuitement un casque de réalité augmentée, mais que finalement vous recevriez simplement un câble HDMI à la place parce que le casque n'est plus en stock !
translation:
Walking away!!!
First order with this merchant and certainly the last! Their business practices are deplorable. Upon placing the order, I noticed they offered a bottle of cologne and a sample with the purchase of the perfume I wanted. However, upon receiving my order, I was surprised to find that the perfume I had purchased came with a sample and another product that had nothing to do with the promised cologne! I contacted customer service to complain, and was simply told that if the product wasn't in the package, it was because it was out of stock. They didn't even bother to contact the customer to inform them! Unacceptable. It's as if they put anything they want as a "gift" to attract more orders and then don't follow through on their promises! It's like if Amazon told you that with the purchase of a PS5, you would receive a reality headset for free, but then you would just receive an HDMI cable instead because the headset is out of stock!

context: English Breakfast Loose Leaf Tea is a full-bodied blend by Taylors of Harrogate, offering a rich and refreshing taste with a bright color. Enjoyable at any time, it's made from black tea leaves and comes in an elegant, reusable 4.41 ounce tin. Carbon Neutral Certified and Ethical Tea Partnership member.
content:
Enttäuschende Qualität
Dies war wieder einmal der Fall, dass ich mich von der Menge der guten (wenn auch teilweise etwas nichtssagenden) Rezensionen habe blenden lassen und die wenigen negativen großzügig überlesen habe. Wobei gerade in letzteren einige sachliche Dinge angesprochen werden, die mich hätten stutzig machen sollen.
Ein Tee, dessen Konsistenz derart ist, dass ein großer Teil der "Blätter" als Pulver leicht durch das Teesieb geht, ist einfach nicht mein Fall. So etwas beeinträchtigt die Qualität des Aufgusses extrem. Und der Tee nimmt sehr schnell (< 3 min) einen sehr bitteren Geschmack an. Brüht man kürzer, schmeckt er ziemlich fad. Mit Papierfiltern mag das besser funktionieren, aber die benutze ich nicht gerne.
Somit kann ich diesen Tee leider nur als Fehlkauf für mich einordnen,
translation:
Disappointing quality
Once again, I allowed myself to be blinded by the multitude of good (though partly somewhat unspecific) reviews and carelessly overlooked the few negative ones. However, it is precisely in these negative reviews that some factual issues are addressed, which should have given me pause.
A tea that has a consistency such that a large part of the "leaves" can easily pass through the tea strainer as powder is simply not my cup of tea. Something like this greatly compromises the quality of the infusion. And the tea quickly takes on a very bitter taste (within < 3 min). If you brew it for a shorter time, it tastes quite bland. Paper filters might work better, but I don't like to use them.
Therefore, I am afraid I can only classify this tea as a purchase mistake for myself.

context: Viajes El Corte Inglés is a travel agency where you can find deals on cheap trips, flights, hotels, vacations, cruises, trains, flight plus hotel, tours, theme parks, Paradores and more.
content:
Cobran dos veces y no te lo devuelven
Estoy esperando dos meses para que me devuelvan 450 euros  que page a la agencia y me lo volvieron a cobrar en el hotel indebidamente  lo reclamé a la agente que me vendió el viaje al director del corte Inglés he llamado por dos veces atención al cliente y no he recibido todavía ni unas disculpas sólo que está en trámites que me contestarán Parece mentira que una empresa como esta tenga esta mala gestión de personal una vergüenza No recomendare y si alguien decide viajar lleven cuidado con lo que les pagan que dicen todo incluido y cuando llegas al hotel te dicen que no lo han pagado que este fue mi caso lo page por dos veces y veremos si no tengo que denunciarlos para cobrar . Hay agencias más serias y profesionales que esta ante una mala operación de un empleo la empresa reponde
translation:
They charge you twice and don't return it to you
I have been waiting for two months for them to return 450 euros that I paid to the agency, and they charged me again at the hotel inappropriately. I have claimed it to the agent who sold me the trip, the director of El Corte Inglés, I have called customer service twice, and I have not yet received even an apology, only that it is being processed and they will answer me. It's hard to believe that a company like this has such poor personnel management, it's a disgrace. I will not recommend it, and if someone decides to travel, be careful with what you pay, as they say it's all included, but when you arrive at the hotel, they tell you that they haven't paid. This happened to me, and I paid twice, and we'll see if I have to report them to get my money back. There are more serious and professional agencies than this one. After a bad operation from an employee, the company should respond.

content:
Pangalusian resort el nido
We had a wonderful five days here at the resort. Staff are incredibly friendly and more than helpful. We chose to stay in a canopy villa, essentially a treehouse accessible by either a ramp, or a tall staircase. The rooms are luxurious and incredibly comfortable. The beach is beautiful a little rocky, and it was pretty windy when we were her.  the pool is not heated but very refreshing and a beautiful place to watch the sunset. We did their sunset hike to get a 360 of all the islands around and that really was beautiful. The hike is not for those out of shape. we met some amazing people, and saw lots of families enjoying their time. 

Are only criticism would be the food. When we first arrived, it was à la cart, which was unbelievable the best ceviche I’ve ever had. However, when it got busy, they switched to only buffet at lunch and dinner which became pretty boring by night 4. in addition, nothing on the buffet was ever hot. Furthermore, a great choice for  Eggs in the morning -made  fresh for you, but again, but often arrived to the table, lukewarm and sometimes cool. 

One tip we only learned about the last day was if you don’t want buffet at lunch you can always order à la cart from the pool bar!

content:
UNA GRAN EXPERIENCIA CON UN GRAN PROFESIONAL
Hoy he ido a comprar a la tienda de Primor del Centro Comercial Parque Principado en Oviedo. Tenia que comprar un regalo muy especial para una adolescente y estaba totalmente perdida. He tenido la gran suerte de encontrar a Wen, para mi un grandisimo profesional. Desde el primer momento me saludo de una manera muy agradable, por lo que nada mas entrar, me hizo sentirme muy agusto, asi que aproveche ( despues de darme una vueta por la tienda, ya que nunca habia estado alli) le pedi por favor si me podria ayudar, a lo cual, muy amablemente me ayudo desde el primer momento, me explicaba cada producto, se interesaba en todo momento para que tipo de persona era, me aconsejaba y me asesoraba e incluso termino asesorandome con productos que me lleve para mi tambien. Hacia tiempo que no encontraba a un gran profesional, asi que desde aqui le doy las gracias por su dedicacion, su amabilidad y su gran asesoramiento. Por supuesto volvere. Muchas gracias Wen.
translation:
A GREAT EXPERIENCE WITH A GREAT PROFESSIONAL
Today I went to buy at the Primor store in the Parque Principado shopping center in Oviedo. I had to buy a very special gift for a teenager and I was completely lost. I was very lucky to meet Wen, in my opinion a great professional. From the very beginning, he welcomed me in a very pleasant way, which made me feel very comfortable as soon as I entered, so I took advantage (after taking a tour of the store, as I had never been there before) I asked him if he could help me, to which he kindly helped me from the first moment, explaining each product, being interested in what type of person it was for, advising and guiding me, and even ended up advising me on products that I took for myself as well. I hadn't found such a great professional in a long time, so from here I thank him for his dedication, kindness, and great advice. Of course, I will be back. Thank you very much Wen.

content:
Useful service but terrible app
The app is extremely slow and buggy. It takes a few seconds to load anything in the app which can be extremely annoying when just checking things quickly. Lots of performance issues. When you open up a page of who is staying at your hostel, it must try and load every single person in the list at once rather than lazy loading. So, when I try to view a list of the 80 people staying at my hostel, the app freezes for a good 30 seconds before even showing the list. The messaging functionality is also extremely buggy and every chat is filled with “Is anyone else solo traveling?”, followed by a message like “I didn’t mean to send that” because everyone accidentally hits the quick chat things.

context: Viajes El Corte Inglés is a travel agency where you can find deals on cheap trips, flights, hotels, vacations, cruises, trains, flight plus hotel, tours, theme parks, Paradores and more.
content:
Viajes el corte inglés ingles me siento estafado
Lo primero que quiero decir es que no hagáis una compra de viajes ni online ni por teléfono con el corte inglés y ahora os explico el porqué. Estando en casa me puse a mirar viajes vi un crucero muy interesante de costa cruceros a un precio interesante también, al ver que era por el corte inglés pedí presupuesto y al día siguiente me llamaron. Me atendió una chica super maja, ella se ofreció a todo a mandarme páginas para coger las excursiones mas baratas, me llamaba a todas horas me enviaba correos con otras ofertas entonces decidí reservar con ella ojo!!!! Con ella!!!! Me lo puso todo tan fácil me dijo que cualquier duda con el check in ella me lo solucionaba que si tenia dudas sobre el barco la llamase la llamase? Donde? Si una vez que as pagado y ya tienes la reserva nunca mas puedes volver a hablar con el departamentos de reservas ni contestan a los correos ya as pagado y adios muy buenas!!!!! Lo mas fuerte que después te pasan a otro departamento si tienes alguna duda en el cual no saben nada ni explicarte como va el tema del seguro de viaje que tambien hemos contratado con ellos ni cambiarte la hora del check in, que nos hubiera gustado cambiarla ya que llegábamos muy temprano un tal alvaro me cogio el teléfono me atendió fatal no me soluciono nada entonces decido llamar a costa cruceros y me llevo la sorpresa de que me dicen: Usted a reservado con una agencia de viajes ante cualquier duda ellos se hacen cargo nosotros no podemos ayudarle!!!!!! Para mi experiencia nunca mas con viajes el corte inglés y mucho menos por la venta teléfonica una pena pero esa a sido mi experiencia solo me toca esperar a que alguien me contacte y me pueda solucionar las dudas ya que salimos de Cruceros en 20 dias
translation:
I feel defrauded by Viajes el Corte Inglés's travel purchase
Firstly, I want to say that you should not make a travel purchase, either online or by phone, with Viajes el Corte Inglés, and now I will explain why. While at home, I was looking at trips and saw a very interesting cruise from Costa Cruceros at an interesting price. I saw that it was through Viajes el Corte Inglés, so I asked for a quote and the next day they called me back. A very nice girl attended me, she offered to help me and send me pages to find the cheapest excursions, she called and emailed me frequently. I decided to book with her, but beware!!!! With her!!!! She made everything so easy, saying that she would help me with any check-in doubts, and if I had any doubts about the boat, I should call her. However, once you've paid and have a reservation, you can no longer contact the reservations department, and they don't respond to emails. After that, they transfer you to another department if you have any doubts, where they know nothing and can't explain the travel insurance we also contracted with them, nor can they change your check-in time, which we would have liked to change because we were arriving very early. I called a person named Alvaro, who answered the phone badly and didn't solve anything. I then called Costa Cruceros and was surprised that they said: "You made a reservation through a travel agency, so they are in charge of any doubts, we can't help you!!!!!" For my experience, I will never use Viajes el Corte Inglés again, especially with phone sales. It's a shame, but that was my experience. I can only wait for someone to contact me and clarify my doubts, as we are leaving on the cruise in 20 days.

context: Shein is an online fashion retailer known for its extensive range of trendy clothing, accessories, and footwear at affordable prices. Catering to a global audience, it offers diverse styles for men, women, and children, with frequent new arrivals and promotions, making it popular among fashion-forward shoppers.
content:
Ich habe früher gerne bei SHEIN bestellt und war immer sehr zufrieden. Habe tolle Baumwollpullover von dort… 
Mittlerweile bin ich sehr enttäuscht und erschrocken über die Angebote. Seit die Influencer Werbung für SHEIN machen, lässt die Qualität der Ware sehr zu wünschen übrig und die Preise wurden sehr angezogen. 
- Zusätzlich muss man wirklich sehr genau hinsehen! - Ich möchte einen Pullover aus Baumwolle bestellen und gucke in die Produktbeschreibung. Dort steht: 
Material Baumwolle
Zusammensetzung 100% Polyester!!
Was soll das? Baumwolle und Polyester haben nichts miteinander zu tun. Eine Frechheit! 
Leider hat mich SHEIN als Kundin verloren.
translation:
I used to enjoy shopping on SHEIN and was always very satisfied. I have bought nice cotton sweaters from there...
Now I am very disappointed and shocked by their offers. Since influencers started promoting SHEIN, the quality of the items has greatly diminished and the prices have increased.
- You really have to pay close attention! - I wanted to order a cotton pullover and checked the product description. It said:
Material: Cotton
Composition: 100% Polyester!!
What's that? Cotton and polyester have nothing to do with each other. A cheek!
Unfortunately, SHEIN has lost me as a customer.

Viajamos a Egipto y en el circuito “Cleopatra I” nos vendieron una cosa y nos dieron otra. Pagamos suplementos por mejoras en el crucero por el Nilo y por los hoteles y eran nefastos. Los servicios de la mayorista mapa tours horrible, nos faltaron comidas, nos cobraron por excursiones que se suponía que estaban en el itinerario, etc. 
Encima a la vuelta, nos cambian el vuelo, a un vuelo de bajo coste el cual salió 5 horas más tarde, perdiendo así las conexiones y vuelos a casa.
Habiendo hecho las pertinentes reclamaciones, no nos devuelven absolutamente nada.
Horror como agencia de viaje, no volveremos a contratar nada con ellos, la atención post-viaje un infierno.
translation:
We traveled to Egypt, and they sold us one thing and gave us another on the "Cleopatra I" circuit. We paid for upgrades for the Nile cruise and hotels, and they were awful. The tour operator, map tours, was horrible. Meals were missing, they charged us for excursions that were supposed to be included in the itinerary, etc.
On the way back, they changed our flight to a low-cost airline, which took off 5 hours later, causing us to miss our connections and flights home.
After making proper complaints, we were not refunded anything.
Terrible travel agency, we will not hire anything from them again. Post-trip attention was a nightmare.

context: Jelife Bento Lunch Box for Kids is a large, leakproof lunchbox with 4 compartments and silverware, ideal for school. Its silicone ring and sauce compartments ensure freshness and prevent mess. Featuring kid-friendly latches and made of food-safe, high-quality materials, it's microwave and dishwasher safe for easy use and cleaning.
content:
Good inexpensive option, perhaps best for elementary and up.
These are a good size and the plastic seems high quality. I particularly like the space for dipping sauce, and the inclusion of all three utensils. The utensils are well made themselves. I also like the subtle variations within the color scheme applied to the various components.
So far it seems to hold up well in the microwave and dishwasher. In our early uses, the dipping sauce has stayed mostly contained during travel. A few specks of sauce may make it into the other compartments but it is tolerable so far and doesn't escape the overall box.
The containers really are extra deep for a higher capacity. I got this for my preschool-aged kids and I don't think they really need the extra capacity yet. The size seems to be more suited to an elementary kid or beyond. Still it may be helpful for certain rounder items like a piece of fruit.
Overall these seem very strong, however I am concerned about a few weak spots. The side flaps seem like the kind of thing which could weaken or come off after extensive use. Also the lid that constrains the utensils has a very small plastic peg that keeps it closed. This peg seems like it could be a weak spot as well. So far these are just speculative concerns, so not a penalty just sharing my perspective. These may also be a reason to use these more with older kids who can take care of them.
translation:
Good inexpensive option, perhaps best for elementary and up.
These are a good size and the plastic seems high quality. I particularly like the space for dipping sauce, and the inclusion of all three utensils. The utensils are well made themselves. I also like the subtle variations within the color scheme applied to the various components.
So far it seems to hold up well in the microwave and dishwasher. In our early uses, the dipping sauce has stayed mostly contained during travel. A few specks of sauce may make it into the other compartments but it is tolerable so far and doesn't escape the overall box.
The containers really are extra deep for a higher capacity. I got this for my preschool-aged kids and I don't think they really need the extra capacity yet. The size seems to be more suited to an elementary kid or beyond. Still it may be helpful for certain rounder items like a piece of fruit.
Overall these seem very strong, however I am concerned about a few weak spots. The side flaps seem like the kind of thing which could weaken or come off after extensive use. Also the lid that constrains the utensils has a very small plastic peg that keeps it closed. This peg seems like it could be a weak spot as well. So far these are just speculative concerns, so not a penalty just sharing my perspective. These may also be a reason to use these more with older kids who can take care of them.

content:

Gave Netflix a ring to explain how unfair this is and they say I cannot go back to £7.99.  Spoke to a manager but he did not care just said nothing we can do but admitted they have no way of knowing if this ad plan will be compatible with your tv.  DISGUSTING, seems like this is a way to get their customers to change to a plan that does not work then charge an extra £3 a month when they try to revert back to a plan you have had for 10 years.  Wish I could give them a minus, so angry, total rip-off, so bye bye Netflix, not that they care.

content:
Slechte klachtenbehandeling
Ik bestel hier al JAREN! JAREN! Nooit een probleem gehad, nooit een klacht doorgestuurd. Dan zet ik een recensie op internet en doen ze alsof ze je willen helpen. Ik heb meer dan 3x fotos moeten sturen en elke keer na een bericht met ‘je krijgt antwoord binnen 2-3 werkdagen’ steeds na meer dan 10 werkdagen zelf een bericht moeten sturen om te vragen voor antwoord. translation:
Poor complaint handling
I have been ordering here for YEARS! YEARS! Never had a problem, never forwarded a complaint. Then I post a review on the internet and they act like they want to help you. I have had to send more than 3 photos and every time after a message saying 'you will receive a response within 2-3 working days', I always have to send a message again after more than 10 working days to ask for a reply. I, and certainly my family and friends, will never order here again. Then you buy a product that costs more than 50 eu and you can throw it in the trash right away.

context: T6 True Wireless Earbuds is a Bluetooth 5.3 headset featuring touch controls and a wireless charging case. With IPX8 waterproofing, it offers smart touch control for music and calls, one-step pairing, and up to 45 hours of playtime. The deep bass and premium design come in Rose Gold.
content:
Auriculares de color vibrante y buenas características
Llevo un par de años usando los Auriculares Inalámbricos TOZO T6 , todavía funcionan perfectamente y puedo decir que no solo me cautivan por su color rosa;
Puntos Fuertes:
Sonido de Alta Calidad con Graves Profundos: Los TOZO T6 entregan un sonido nítido y potente, destacándose por sus graves profundos. Esta calidad de audio inmersiva hace que disfrutar de la música, podcasts o llamadas sea una experiencia excepcional.
Control Táctil Intuitivo: La interfaz de control táctil facilita la gestión de llamadas y reproducción de música sin tener que buscar botones físicos. Esta característica añade comodidad y modernidad a la experiencia de uso.
IPX8 Impermeable: La clasificación de resistencia al agua IPX8 hace que estos auriculares sean ideales para actividades deportivas y climas húmedos. Pueden sumergirse hasta 1 metro de profundidad durante un período prolongado sin sufrir daños, proporcionando una durabilidad excepcional.
Carga Inalámbrica y Duración de Batería: La posibilidad de cargar los auriculares de forma inalámbrica es un toque de lujo que se suma a su atractivo. Además, la impresionante duración de la batería de hasta 45 horas garantiza un uso prolongado sin preocupaciones de quedarse sin energía.
Conexión Bluetooth 5.3 Estable: La tecnología Bluetooth 5.3 asegura una conexión estable y de alta calidad, minimizando las interrupciones y ofreciendo una experiencia de audio sin problemas.
Puntos Débiles:
Si tengo que poner alguna pega diría que el tamaño de la funda de carga puede ser para algunos usuarios un poco voluminosa en comparación con otros modelos en el mercado. Esto podría afectar la portabilidad para algunos usuarios.
En resumen, los veo altamente recomendables
Espero que te haya sido de utilidad la reseña :)
translation:
Headphones with vibrant color and good features
I have been using TOZO T6 Wireless Headphones for a couple of years now, and they still work perfectly; I can tell you that they are not just appealing due to their pink color.
Pros:
High-Quality Sound with Deep Bass: The TOZO T6 delivers clear and powerful sound, standing out for its deep bass. This immersive audio quality makes enjoying music, podcasts, or calls an exceptional experience.
Intuitive Touch Control: The touch control interface facilitates call management and music playback without the need to search for physical buttons. This feature adds convenience and modernity to the user experience.
IPX8 Waterproof: With an IPX8 water resistance rating, these headphones are ideal for sports activities and humid climates. They can be submerged up to 1 meter deep for an extended period without suffering damage, providing exceptional durability.
Wireless Charging and Battery Life: The ability to wirelessly charge the headphones is a luxurious touch that adds to their appeal. Furthermore, the impressive battery life of up to 45 hours ensures prolonged use without worrying about running out of power.
Stable Bluetooth 5.3 Connection: Bluetooth 5.3 technology ensures a stable and high-quality connection, minimizing interruptions and offering a seamless audio experience.
Cons:
If I have to mention a drawback, I would say that the size of the charging case can be a bit bulky compared to other models on the market. This could affect portability for some users.
In conclusion, I highly recommend them
I hope you found this review helpful :)

content:
Pesima atención al cliente en pedidos online
El día 28 de enero hice un pedido online y casi dos semanas esperando me decido a mirar el estado de mi pedido y pone que ha sido entregado el día 1 de febrero . Me pongo en contacto con el servicio de atención al Cliente para decir que mi pedido no ha llegado y me dicen que van a hablar con la empresa de transporte. Al día siguiente me llama un transportista y me dice que yo le dije que lo dejara en el felpudo cuando me llamo por teléfono porque no estábamos en casa. He mandado pantallazo de las llamadas telefónicas y de las llamadas al telefonillo de la casa y ese día no me llamo nadie a ninguno de los sitios. TENGO PRUEBAS DE QUE NO LO HAN ENTREGADO. Y aún me contesta primor que el transportista se pasará a hablar conmigo para aclararlo… no confiéis en esta tienda para hacer pedidos porque no se hacen responsables si ocurre algo con el transporte. Es una vergüenza
translation:
Terrible customer service in online orders
On January 28, I placed an online order and, after almost two weeks of waiting, I decide to check the status of my order and it shows that it was delivered on February 1st. I contact the customer service to inform them that my order has not arrived and they tell me that they will speak with the transportation company. The next day, a transportation agent calls me and tells me that I told him to leave it on the doormat when he called me by phone because we were not at home. I have sent screenshots of the phone calls and of the calls to the apartment intercom and that day no one called either of the places. I HAVE PROOF THAT IT WAS NOT DELIVERED. And they still tell me that the transportation agent will contact me to clarify it... do not trust this store for orders because they do not take responsibility if something happens with the transportation. It's a shame.

context: Jelife Bento Lunch Box for Kids is a large, leakproof lunchbox with 4 compartments and silverware, ideal for school. Its silicone ring and sauce compartments ensure freshness and prevent mess. Featuring kid-friendly latches and made of food-safe, high-quality materials, it's microwave and dishwasher safe for easy use and cleaning.
content:
Portion control...
First off let me just say that I know this lunch box is meant for kids BUT I am not a big eater and try to portion control what I eat and how much -- so this does the trick. I could nicely fit a whole sandwich along with 2 clementine tangerines and grapes... AWESOME! The center area is perfect for salad dressing if you have a small salad or some carrot sticks. The silicone ring keeps it leak proof and has a nice snug fit once you snap on the lid. I like the compartments that separate everything as I don't like my food getting "mixed up" with each other while transporting. With that said, if it's good enough for this adult... it'll be great for kids! I highly recommend!

context: Tripadvisor is a travel platform providing reviews, recommendations, and bookings for hotels, restaurants, attractions, and experiences worldwide. Users can browse millions of traveler reviews, compare prices, and make reservations directly through the app.
content:
If you are looking for a holiday in Goa, this may not be for you
We booked two nights at the Plantation having read such good reviews. However, once we arrived we found the host patronising and unwelcoming. We were not prepared for how many dogs would be on the property (five) and they were aggressive and extremely loud, disturbing the sense of peacefulness amidst nature. 

The pool was lovely, however the cabins were rudimentary at best. Extremely old and uncomfortable bedding with just one pillow, and the whole room looked bleak.  

Whilst it’s not a hotel and we didn’t expect 5* service, we were surprised to see the host watch us drag our bags from the taxi to the cabin without any offer of help. 

The food was mediocre at best, and late served - which was particularly frustrating when they did not have alternative food to order and one-hour meal times were strictly defined in the guest documents. 

We did not appreciate the host trying to hard sell his cashew liquor at every opportunity. He was completely disinterested in his guests, rather spoke at us at length about his business and how tourism is ruining Goa. Ironic,  considering his decision to offer accommodation to tourists. 

Also considering Goa is dark after 6pm, the lighting in our cabins was very poor, which made it very hard to read, and there is absolutely nothing else to do in the evenings (Wi-Fi doesn’t reach the rooms and you are isolated in the forest).

To top it all off, when we paid for our dinner and drinks, the host failed to return the correct change. If you are looking for an enjoyable stay in Goa, this may not be for you. However, the guide Sam (organised through the host) who took us on a jungle hike to see the waterfall was FANTASTIC and we would highly recommend him. He knew about every single animal, was extremely respectful of nature, and a delight to talk to.
translation:
If you are looking for a holiday in Goa, this may not be for you
We booked two nights at the Plantation having read such good reviews. However, once we arrived we found the host patronising and unwelcoming. We were not prepared for how many dogs would be on the property (five) and they were aggressive and extremely loud, disturbing the sense of peacefulness amidst nature. 

The pool was lovely, however the cabins were rudimentary at best. Extremely old and uncomfortable bedding with just one pillow, and the whole room looked bleak.  

Whilst it’s not a hotel and we didn’t expect 5* service, we were surprised to see the host watch us drag our bags from the taxi to the cabin without any offer of help. 

The food was mediocre at best, and late served - which was particularly frustrating when they did not have alternative food to order and one-hour meal times were strictly defined in the guest documents. 

We did not appreciate the host trying to hard sell his cashew liquor at every opportunity. He was completely disinterested in his guests, rather spoke at us at length about his business and how tourism is ruining Goa. Ironic,  considering his decision to offer accommodation to tourists. 

Also considering Goa is dark after 6pm, the lighting in our cabins was very poor, which made it very hard to read, and there is absolutely nothing else to do in the evenings (Wi-Fi doesn’t reach the rooms and you are isolated in the forest).

To top it all off, when we paid for our dinner and drinks, the host failed to return the correct change. If you are looking for an enjoyable stay in Goa, this may not be for you. However, the guide Sam (organised through the host) who took us on a jungle hike to see the waterfall was FANTASTIC and we would highly recommend him. He knew about every single animal, was extremely respectful of nature, and a delight to talk to.

content:
Trato nefasto primor plaza mayor
Acabo de ir a comprar a primor de plaza mayor, iba a gastarme 300 euros y he salido sin nada por las malas formas que ha tenido conmigo la empleada que se encuentra en la zona de cremas cuando le he preguntado si nos regalarían algún neceser por esa compra, su respuesta, con muy malas formas, fue: “ no tenemos neceseres, te daré unas muestras de perfumes, además, por la compra de dos perfumes tampoco damos neceseres”. Incierto porque compraba 2 perfumes y una crema, más un champú y acondicionador de parafarmacia, un total de 300 euros.. y cuando viene la encargada lo empeora, dándole la razón a la empleada y dejándome avergonzada como si estuviera mendigando un neceser. Increíble, he puesto una reclamación y mañana la llevaré a consumo. Hay personas que no están cualificadas para estar cara al público y lo de la encargada ha sido de traca, creo que no sabe que su labor es actuar objetivamente y no decirme q ella conoce a la empleada y que seguro q tiene razón y me ha hablado bien, sin haber presenciado la conversación.
translation:
Disgraceful treatment in Primor Plaza Mayor
I just went to Primor at Plaza Mayor to spend 300 euros, but I left empty-handed due to the rude behavior of the employee in the cream section. I asked if they would give me a cosmetic bag with my purchase, and she rudely replied, "We don't have cosmetic bags. I can give you some perfume samples. Also, we don't give cosmetic bags even when you buy two perfumes." This is uncertain because I was buying 2 perfumes, a cream, a shampoo, and a conditioner from the parapharmacy, a total of 300 euros. The situation worsened when the supervisor agreed with the employee, embarrassing me as if I were begging for a cosmetic bag. Unbelievable, I have filed a complaint and will bring it to consumer affairs tomorrow. There are people who are not qualified to be customer-facing, and the supervisor's behavior has been outrageous. I think she doesn't realize that her job is to act objectively and not to tell me that she knows the employee and that she's probably right and has spoken well of me, without having witnessed the conversation.

context: Cloudflare is an internet security and performance company, offering services like content delivery network (CDN), DDoS mitigation, and DNS management. Trusted by millions of websites, it enhances security, reliability, and speed, protecting against cyber threats and ensuring seamless online experiences for users globally.
content:
My SOP part number 2? Setting up Cloudflare. If it's .com, it probably goes to number 1 in the process of creating a website.

I've achieved ~98% cache ratio every month here (Pro version, yes), which is amazing.

For the people complaining about this "hosting company", since when is Cloudflare a hosting company?

Your site stopped working after moving to Cloudflare? 
Well, it's the fastest DNS I've worked with, but still, it needs propagation. Or a professional to do what you don't know.

Cat abuse?
I don't agree with that practice, but if they take a stance on every situation like that, they would be playing god pretty fast.

TL;DR: Cloudflare gives you better security, if you know what you're doing (and 20/25$ for the pro version compared to the competition is nothing, with only BunnyCDN offering better prices, but I would rather use Cloudflare any day) you can pretty much cache all your site on their servers, (...).

Just use it.
And if you don't know how to "make it work" properly, just hire a professional as that takes less than 1h to configure.

Everyone is super cheap and items I post here are already like $5-10 and even some $2 just to get rid of. The uploading process is not that great. Like getting your hopes up because they don’t often buy them after offering so why offer on the first place. The only thing I like is that the price that you sell it for is what you will make so it’s easy to see. But right now I finally had a $2.50 sale last night but the label is no where! I’ve emailed support for help this morning, it’s been 10 hours already and they haven’t gotten back. It’s ridiculous. I do not add new items because of the slow sales and cheapskates on here. I’m just waiting to see if I can sell the rest of whatever is on here then delete it. I don’t recommend this app.

content:
Phishing websites hosted on Cloudflare
Dear Cloudflare,

I hope this message finds you amidst a commitment to maintaining the highest standards of security and integrity. Unfortunately, I am compelled to bring a pressing matter to your attention, which poses a serious threat to the safety and privacy of users on your platform.

It has recently come to our notice that a website hosted on Cloudflare.com is engaged in highly malicious activities. This particular website is shamelessly impersonating our organization and employing deceptive tactics to spam social media users. The malicious intent behind this impersonation is to lure unsuspecting users into providing sensitive billing information, a clear violation of copyright and trademark laws.

The gravity of such actions cannot be overstated, as they not only infringe upon legal boundaries but also compromise the trust and security of individuals who fall victim to these deceptive practices. Given the severity of the situation, we urgently request your immediate intervention to take down all copyrighted materials associated with the fraudulent website.

Furthermore, we implore you to initiate a comprehensive investigation into the hosting details of this website. It is imperative to identify and rectify any fraudulent activities promptly to safeguard the interests of innocent users who may unknowingly become victims of this illicit scheme.

Your swift and decisive action in this matter is of utmost importance to curb the potential harm caused by the website's illicit activities. We believe that Cloudflare, as a responsible hosting provider, will prioritize the security and well-being of its users.

We sincerely hope that you understand the urgency of this situation and take the necessary measures to address and rectify the ongoing threats. Your cooperation in resolving this critical issue promptly is appreciated.

Thank you for your immediate attention to this matter.

translation: A genuine travel disaster with El Corte Inglés online. context: Viajes El Corte Inglés is a travel agency where you can find deals on cheap trips, flights, hotels, vacations, cruises, trains, flight plus hotel, tours, theme parks, Paradores and more.
content:
La venta online es pésima. Gran interés y prisa por vender el paquete vacacional pero escasos conocimientos al respecto de la calidad de lo que están vendiendo y nula responsabilidad si algo sale mal. Hicimos un viaje a Punta Cana con un hotel que cambió a última hora porque cerraba para reformar . El que lo sustituyó no estaba mucho mejor. Los vuelos cambiaron también la fecha de salida y tuvimos que comprar los enlaces a la ciudad de salida dos veces. No se hicieron cargo de nada y cuando solicitamos responsabilidad al Corte Inglés nos dicen que son departamentos diferentes. Sólo hemos conseguido un correo con un escueto “lo sentimos”. 
Yo no voy a volver a contratar ningún viaje a través de la web ni en veta telefónica.
translation:
Online shopping is terrible. High interest and eagerness to sell the vacation package, but little knowledge of the quality of what they're selling, and no responsibility taken if something goes wrong. We took a trip to Punta Cana with a hotel that changed last minute because it was closing for renovations. The replacement wasn't much better. Flight dates also changed, and we had to purchase connecting flights to the departure city twice. They took no responsibility for it, and when we requested accountability from El Corte Inglés, they said they were different departments. We have only received a brief "we're sorry" email.
I will not be booking any more trips through their website or over the phone.

context: Jelife Bento Lunch Box for Kids is a large, leakproof lunchbox with 4 compartments and silverware, ideal for school. Its silicone ring and sauce compartments ensure freshness and prevent mess. Featuring kid-friendly latches and made of food-safe, high-quality materials, it's microwave and dishwasher safe for easy use and cleaning.
content:
I have a love/hate relationship with this box
I wanted to love this box. It has the perfect sized compartments we needed. It comes with reusable silverware and the color choices are cute. The price was also very reasonable. Unfortunately, my kids have had issues with these and we've had to replace them more than once. We have broken the locking tabs on the side, we have had things leak into other compartments because the seal wasn't tight, we have snapped the lid to the silverware compartment clean off, etc. Now, I understand that some of these things are definitely due to my kids being too rough and that's fine. I wasn't expecting these to last more than 1 school year anyway.  But it would have been nice if it was a little sturdier.  Regardless, my kids absolutely loved them and insisted I buy replacements. Just know that if your child is rough on things, this will not last you long.

content:
Primor estafadores NO COMPREN A ESTA GENTE
La situación sigue igual, después de mi comentario por este medio, me contactaron por correo ofreciéndome varias opciones para la devolución, entre ellas la de que un repartidor fuese a una dirección que yo les tengo que facilitar y en una franja horaria para recoger el paquete, me pidieron todos los datos del pedido y referencia de los artículos( cabe destacar que ni en la web ni el el ticket de compra que viene en el correo ni en el documento que venía en el paquete traía esos datos) hice fotos de los códigos de barra.
De esto hace más de una semana que envié esos datos y sigo sin obtener respuesta, ni han ido a recoger el paquete. 
Que vergüenza de empresa. Les he dado una semana si no me responden y me recogen el paquete acudiré a las autoridades para hacer la denuncia formal por estafa.
translation:
Primor scammers DON'T BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE
The situation remains the same, after my comment through this medium, they contacted me by email offering several options for the refund, among them that a delivery person would go to an address that I have to provide and in a time slot to pick up the package, they asked me for all the order data and reference of the items (it is worth mentioning that neither on the web nor on the purchase ticket that comes in the email nor in the document that came in the package had those data) I took pictures of the barcodes.
A week has passed since I sent that information and I still have not received a response, nor have they gone to pick up the package.
What a disgrace of a company. I have given them a week if they do not respond and come to pick up the package I will go to the authorities to make a formal complaint for fraud.

context: Netflix is a subscription-based streaming service offering a vast library of movies, TV shows, documentaries, and original content across various genres. With a user-friendly interface, it provides on-demand entertainment accessible on multiple devices, catering to diverse viewer preferences worldwide.
content:
A High Srandard of Mediocrity
I liked the user interface. It's solid, easy and intuitive to find your way around. There are no tedious adverts and everything has subtitles so I can watch programmes in bed at night without waking up the wife!
I really liked many of the series. Quality drama from many countries and cultures and in their native languages (subtitles). Only BBC iPlayer is better for series. And Free.

Documentaries are non-existent,  so don't expect to improve your mind

The main gripe I have is the films. There ARE films on there worth your time watching. But very few of them. The majority are dire chewing gum for the eyes to entertain the undiscerning. 

Formulaic, repetitive plotlines, low budget, unknown cast, predictive plot lines. If I want to watch a film I always have better success with Film 4, or there's TPTV for the true classics. 
If you try searching for a film 80% of the time you get a "we don't have that, try this load of Straight-to-DVD crap".

I've got a few months left on my contract, then I will review. Overall I'm rather "meh"
translation:
A High Srandard of Mediocrity
I liked the user interface. It's solid, easy and intuitive to find your way around. There are no tedious adverts and everything has subtitles so I can watch programmes in bed at night without waking up the wife!
I really liked many of the series. Quality drama from many countries and cultures and in their native languages (subtitles). Only BBC iPlayer is better for series. And Free.

Documentaries are non-existent,  so don't expect to improve your mind

The main gripe I have is the films. There ARE films on there worth your time watching. But very few of them. The majority are dire chewing gum for the eyes to entertain the undiscerning. 

Formulaic, repetitive plotlines, low budget, unknown cast, predictive plot lines. If I want to watch a film I always have better success with Film 4, or there's TPTV for the true classics. 
If you try searching for a film 80% of the time you get a "we don't have that, try this load of Straight-to-DVD crap".

I've got a few months left on my contract, then I will review. Overall I'm rather "meh"
